body:
@ijuma in streams, there is currently a mix of 1) `throws Exceptions` and 2) `throws SpecificException` It would be nice, but it's not a must-have, to do this consistently. It's a fair question on what best practices are. We could do it consistently by having all be (1) or (2). Again, not a show stopper either way. 

I am currently looking at exception handling end to end in streams, and I personally prefer (2). I don't think we need to codify this in checkStyle or anything like that, but @evis just did a nice job with the cleanup and I'd hate losing it.

Having said that, perhaps in cases when multiple exceptions are expected we can just throw their superclass, `Exceptions` since it might be an overkill to throw all.
